cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision and deep learning techniques for the classification of chest radiographs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the performance of different neural network architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential applications of these techniques in healthcare, which could make it relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as well. Finally, the paper deals with image analysis, which could also make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
